The paper focuses on embedding neural networks into material robots for autonomous operation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of machine learning tools and deep neural networks also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of microcontrollers for computation, which falls under the embedded systems (cs.EM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the approach using multiple examples, which suggests a connection to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
